snippet.title: Loaded Pita Nachos
snippet.description: Everyone will love these Loaded Pita Nachos with their combination of spicy chili, rich sour cream and melted cheddar cheese.

snippet.title: White Bean Pesto Dip with Pita Chips
snippet.description: Perfect for entertaining, this unique white bean dip features delicious and distinctive pesto flavors and takes just 10 minutes to prepare. Serve with pita chips or other crispy crackers.

snippet.title: Nesquik Nachos
snippet.description: Nesquik Nachos are a fun and simple treat that you'll love to make. Good for parties and summertime entertaining too!

snippet.title: Spinach Artichoke Dip
snippet.description: If you are entertaining or looking for quick and tasty appetizer to bring to a pot-luck, this Spinach Artichoke Dip will surely be a hit and best of all it’s a snap to put together. Read more about this recipe on the Nestlé Kitchens blog .

snippet.title: Roasted Red Pepper and White Bean Dip
snippet.description: A creamy dip with roasted red peppers and spicy jalapeños. A great addition to your next party. Look for roasted red bell peppers in the vegetable aisle or produce section of your supermarket, or roast your own!

snippet.title: Snackin' Pumpkin Hummus
snippet.description: This delicious snack takes only minutes to prepare. Try this pumpkin hummus coupled with warm pita bread or crisp vegetables and you're sure to fall in love with this creamy dip, perfect for both snacking and entertaining.

snippet.title: Chutney Salsa
snippet.description: Chutney is a tasty east Indian condiment that lends itself well to other dishes and cuisines. Here, it spices up a chunky salsa, making it a great complement to any main dish. Look for chutney in the pickle or condiment aisle of your supermarket.

snippet.title: Hummus + Pumpkin
snippet.description: By adding Libby’s® 100% Pure Pumpkin to refrigerated classic hummus, per 2 tablespoon serving you can reduce the calories by 20, total fat by 1.5 grams, sodium by 40mg and add a good source of vitamin A. Pumpkin adds a touch of color and light earthiness to the flavor of hummus.

snippet.title: Bean and Spinach Dip
snippet.description: This Bean and Spinach Dip is both quick and tasty. Serve with pita bread slices or crunchy tortilla chips. Keep these ingredients on hand for unexpected guests and you'll always have something delicious to serve.

snippet.title: Pesto Kale Chips
snippet.description: Pesto Kale Chips are a real treat! Drizzled with pesto and then baked to bring out delicious new flavors and exciting textures, this recipe is a great way to introduce this popular and abundant vegetable.
